Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on September 01, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Compulsions can be physical or mental. CBTschool.com @kimberleyquinlan'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on September 01, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Compulsions are anything that is done to immediately remove the anxiety, doubt, physical discomfort, or uncertainty that comes from obsessions. CBTschool.com @kimberleyquinlan'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on September 01, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Physical compulsions might include: doing something a specific number of times (washing your hands, taking a sip of water), picking at your skin, doing things "just right" (stacking the dishes, folding the laundry CBTschool.com @kimberleyquinlan'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on September 01, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Avoidant Compulsions might include: Avoiding any person, object, substance, thought, or or place that triggers the obsession CBTschool.com @kimberleyquinlan'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on September 01, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Mental compulsions might include: rumination, mental "reviewing" of past events, checking (your attraction level, how your body feels, what emotions you are feeling) CBTschool.com @kimberleyquinlan'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on September 01, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Reassurance compulsions include: Googling asking loved ones questions, frequently visiting doctors or professionals related to your obsession, etc. CBTschool.com @kimberleyquinlan'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on September 01, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'The only way to break the obsessive-compulsive cycle is to practice uncertainty and discomfort. CBTschool.com @kimberleyquinlan'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on September 01, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'When you have the urge to do a compulsion, you can thank it for trying to keep you safe, but let it know that's not necessary. You're not in danger. CBTschool.com @kimberleyquinlan'.
Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on September 01, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, furniture and text that says 'ERP School A Compassionate Online Course for OCD Linkin Bio @kimberleyquinlan'.

Repeat after me THOUGHTS ARE NOT FACTS. Just because we think something doesn’t make it any more true, yet when we are anxious we mistakenly assume that because we have had a response to the thought, that the thought is true. ❌ This is not the case! Use this space to share any anxious thoughts that have been consuming your mind lately below ⬇️⬇️⬇️
